Definition 7.1. A Segal pre-operad is a dendroidal space $A$ such that $A(\eta)$ is a discrete simplicial set (i.e. all the simplices of positive dimension in $A(\eta)$ are degenerated). We denote by $\mathpzc{PreOper}$ the full subcategory of $\mathpzc{sdSet}$ spanned by Segal pre-operads.
Definition 3.7. Let $f:X\longrightarrow Y$ be a morphism of $\infty$-operads. The map $f$ is fully faithful if, for any $(n+1)$-tuple of $0$-cells $(x_{1},\ldots,x_{n},x)$ in $X$, the morphism $X(x_{1},\ldots,x_{n};x)\longrightarrow Y(f(x_{1}),\ldots,f(x_{n});f(x))$ is a simplicial homotopy equivalence. The map $f$ is essentially surjective if the functor underlying the morphism of operads $\tau_{d}(X)\longrightarrow\tau_{d}(Y)$ is essentially surjective.
Definition 5.9. A morphism of dendroidal Segal spaces $f:X\longrightarrow Y$ is fully faithful if, for any $(n+1)$-tuple of $0$-cells $(x_{1},\ldots,x_{n},x)$ in $X(\eta)$, the morphism $X(x_{1},\ldots,x_{n};x)\longrightarrow Y(f(x_{1}),\ldots,f(x_{n});f(x))$ is a simplicial homotopy equivalence. A morphism of dendroidal Segal spaces is a weak equivalence on objects if its evaluation at $\eta$ is a simplicial weak equivalence.
